{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017qYKVScav7jy7cvooNoiT5","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# F5 Plan\n2\t\n3\t## Acceptance criteria\n4\t\n5\tFrom SPEC §6.1 — **POST /api/events** (single event ingestion):\n6\t\n7\t- `event_name` required.\n8\t- At least one of `device_id` or `user_id` required.\n9\t- `timestamp` optional; defaults to server time.\n10\t- `properties` optional; any flat key-value object.\n11\t- `201 Created` — event stored.\n12\t- `400 Bad Request` — missing required fields. Body: `{ \"error\": \"...\" }`.\n13\t- `409 Conflict` — device already mapped to a different user.\n14\t\n15\tFrom SPEC §5 — Identity resolution write path:\n16\t\n17\t1. Validate: at least one of device_id or user_id must be present.\n18\t2. If timestamp is missing, set to now().\n19\t3. Insert raw event into `events` table.\n20\t4. If BOTH device_id AND user_id are present:\n21\t   a. Check identity_mappings FINAL for this device_id.\n22\t   b. If no mapping exists → INSERT (device_id, user_id).\n23\t   c. If mapping exists with same user_id → no-op (idempotent).\n24\t   d. If mapping exists with different user_id → reject with 409 Conflict.\n25\t\n26\t## Dependencies\n27\t\n28\tCompleted features this builds on (no `F*-done` sentinel files exist, but git history confirms F1–F4 are committed):\n29\t\n30\t- **F1** — `src/lib/clickhouse.ts` (ClickHouse client singleton)\n31\t- **F2** — `scripts/migrate.ts` + `scripts/schema.sql` (database/table creation)\n32\t- **F4** — `src/lib/identity.ts` (validation, identity resolution, event insertion logic)\n33\t\n34\tExact files imported:\n35\t- `src/lib/identity.ts` — `insertEvent`, `IdentityConflictError`\n36\t\n37\t## Files to create or modify\n38\t\n39\t- **CREATE** `src/app/api/events/route.ts` — POST handler for `/api/events`\n40\t\n41\t## Implementation order\n42\t\n43\t1. Create `src/app/api/events/route.ts` with an exported `POST` function that:\n44\t   - Reads the JSON request body.\n45\t   - Calls `insertEvent()` from `src/lib/identity.ts`.\n46\t   - Returns `201` with the inserted event row on success.\n47\t   - Catches validation errors → returns `400` with `{ error: message }`.\n48\t   - Catches `IdentityConflictError` → returns `409` with `{ error: message }`.\n49\t\n50\tThat's it — one file, one function. All business logic already lives in `src/lib/identity.ts`.\n51\t\n52\t## Sprint contract\n53\t\n54\t- [ ] File `src/app/api/events/route.ts` exists and exports a `POST` function\n55\t- [ ] Test suite → `pnpm test` exits with 0 failures\n56\t- [ ] Lint check → `pnpm lint` exits 0\n57\t- [ ] Type check → `pnpm typecheck` exits 0\n58\t- [ ] Build check → `pnpm build` exits 0\n59\t- [ ] **Integration gap**: POST `http://localhost:3000/api/events` with valid body `{\"event_name\":\"Page Viewed\",\"device_id\":\"dev-1\"}` → 201 response with JSON containing `event_id` and `event_name`\n60\t- [ ] **Integration gap**: POST `http://localhost:3000/api/events` with `{\"device_id\":\"dev-1\"}` (missing event_name) → 400 response with JSON containing `error`\n61\t- [ ] **Integration gap**: POST `http://localhost:3000/api/events` with `{\"event_name\":\"X\"}` (missing both identifiers) → 400 response with JSON containing `error`\n62\t\n63\t## Test plan\n64\t\n65\t- **Test file**: `src/app/api/events/__tests__/route.test.ts`\n66\t- **Module under test**: `POST` handler from `src/app/api/events/route.ts`\n67\t- **Cases to cover**:\n68\t  - Returns 201 and JSON body with `event_id`, `event_name`, `resolved_id` when given a valid event with `device_id` only\n69\t  - Returns 201 when given a valid event with `user_id` only\n70\t  - Returns 201 when given a valid event with both `device_id` and `user_id`\n71\t  - Preserves caller-provided `timestamp` in the returned row\n72\t  - Returns 400 with `{ error: \"...\" }` when `event_name` is missing\n73\t  - Returns 400 with `{ error: \"...\" }` when both `device_id` and `user_id` are missing\n74\t  - Returns 409 with `{ error: \"...\" }` when `IdentityConflictError` is thrown by `insertEvent`\n75\t  - Returns 400 when request body is not valid JSON (malformed body)\n76\t\n77\t  Tests mock `insertEvent` and `IdentityConflictError` from `@/lib/identity` — the route handler is a thin HTTP adapter; identity logic is already unit-tested in `src/lib/__tests__/identity.test.ts`.\n78\t\n79\t- **Integration gap**: Full round-trip POST → ClickHouse → response requires a running dev server and ClickHouse instance.\n80\t\n81\t## Risks and open questions\n82\t\n83\tNone. The route handler is a straightforward adapter between HTTP and the already-implemented `insertEvent` function. All edge cases (validation, identity conflict) are handled by the identity module.\n84\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f9a2fb74-865c-47a7-babc-0c049bfc6046","uuid":"85d2f93f-c1d1-43d6-b73d-e023656dea52","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:24:08.465Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/features/F5-plan.md","content":"# F5 Plan\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\nFrom SPEC §6.1 — **POST /api/events** (single event ingestion):\n\n- `event_name` required.\n- At least one of `device_id` or `user_id` required.\n- `timestamp` optional; defaults to server time.\n- `properties` optional; any flat key-value object.\n- `201 Created` — event stored.\n- `400 Bad Request` — missing required fields. Body: `{ \"error\": \"...\" }`.\n- `409 Conflict` — device already mapped to a different user.\n\nFrom SPEC §5 — Identity resolution write path:\n\n1. Validate: at least one of device_id or user_id must be present.\n2. If timestamp is missing, set to now().\n3. Insert raw event into `events` table.\n4. If BOTH device_id AND user_id are present:\n   a. Check identity_mappings FINAL for this device_id.\n   b. If no mapping exists → INSERT (device_id, user_id).\n   c. If mapping exists with same user_id → no-op (idempotent).\n   d. If mapping exists with different user_id → reject with 409 Conflict.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nCompleted features this builds on (no `F*-done` sentinel files exist, but git history confirms F1–F4 are committed):\n\n- **F1** — `src/lib/clickhouse.ts` (ClickHouse client singleton)\n- **F2** — `scripts/migrate.ts` + `scripts/schema.sql` (database/table creation)\n- **F4** — `src/lib/identity.ts` (validation, identity resolution, event insertion logic)\n\nExact files imported:\n- `src/lib/identity.ts` — `insertEvent`, `IdentityConflictError`\n\n## Files to create or modify\n\n- **CREATE** `src/app/api/events/route.ts` — POST handler for `/api/events`\n\n## Implementation order\n\n1. Create `src/app/api/events/route.ts` with an exported `POST` function that:\n   - Reads the JSON request body.\n   - Calls `insertEvent()` from `src/lib/identity.ts`.\n   - Returns `201` with the inserted event row on success.\n   - Catches validation errors → returns `400` with `{ error: message }`.\n   - Catches `IdentityConflictError` → returns `409` with `{ error: message }`.\n\nThat's it — one file, one function. All business logic already lives in `src/lib/identity.ts`.\n\n## Sprint contract\n\n- [ ] File `src/app/api/events/route.ts` exists and exports a `POST` function\n- [ ] Test suite → `pnpm test` exits with 0 failures\n- [ ] Lint check → `pnpm lint` exits 0\n- [ ] Type check → `pnpm typecheck` exits 0\n- [ ] Build check → `pnpm build` exits 0\n- [ ] **Integration gap**: POST `http://localhost:3000/api/events` with valid body `{\"event_name\":\"Page Viewed\",\"device_id\":\"dev-1\"}` → 201 response with JSON containing `event_id` and `event_name`\n- [ ] **Integration gap**: POST `http://localhost:3000/api/events` with `{\"device_id\":\"dev-1\"}` (missing event_name) → 400 response with JSON containing `error`\n- [ ] **Integration gap**: POST `http://localhost:3000/api/events` with `{\"event_name\":\"X\"}` (missing both identifiers) → 400 response with JSON containing `error`\n\n## Test plan\n\n- **Test file**: `src/app/api/events/__tests__/route.test.ts`\n- **Module under test**: `POST` handler from `src/app/api/events/route.ts`\n- **Cases to cover**:\n  - Returns 201 and JSON body with `event_id`, `event_name`, `resolved_id` when given a valid event with `device_id` only\n  - Returns 201 when given a valid event with `user_id` only\n  - Returns 201 when given a valid event with both `device_id` and `user_id`\n  - Preserves caller-provided `timestamp` in the returned row\n  - Returns 400 with `{ error: \"...\" }` when `event_name` is missing\n  - Returns 400 with `{ error: \"...\" }` when both `device_id` and `user_id` are missing\n  - Returns 409 with `{ error: \"...\" }` when `IdentityConflictError` is thrown by `insertEvent`\n  - Returns 400 when request body is not valid JSON (malformed body)\n\n  Tests mock `insertEvent` and `IdentityConflictError` from `@/lib/identity` — the route handler is a thin HTTP adapter; identity logic is already unit-tested in `src/lib/__tests__/identity.test.ts`.\n\n- **Integration gap**: Full round-trip POST → ClickHouse → response requires a running dev server and ClickHouse instance.\n\n## Risks and open questions\n\nNone. The route handler is a straightforward adapter between HTTP and the already-implemented `insertEvent` function. All edge cases (validation, identity conflict) are handled by the identity module.\n","numLines":84,"startLine":1,"totalLines":84}}}
